Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.05,0:15:50.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}有着我们非常熟悉的上下往复运动{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}has an up-and-down motion that's very familiar to us.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.72,0:15:53.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}但加州大学伯克利分校的学生将会变化一下{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}But these UC Berkeley students will switch gears{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.41,0:15:55.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}给我们展示声波是如何的不同{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}and show us how a sound wave is different.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.97,0:15:58.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}好的 大家放好彩球{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}Okay, everyone, lose the pom-poms!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.84,0:16:02.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}由于声波是压力波{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}Since sound waves are pressure waves,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.20,0:16:04.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}我们将请学生们制造一个压力波{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}we're gonna build a pressure wave out of all these students.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.27,0:16:07.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}好的 大家排成一行{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}Okay, everybody, let's line up.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.49,0:16:09.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}肩挨着肩{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}You go over here and then shoulder-to-shoulder{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.13,0:16:10.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}就象这样{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}just like this.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.35,0:16:12.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}一直排下去 不留缺口{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}Stretch out over there a little bit, no gaps.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.44,0:16:15.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}你们等一会要互相碰撞{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}You're gonna be students colliding with each other{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.77,0:16:19.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}就象声波里的分子去互相碰撞{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}like molecules colliding in a sound wave.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.99,0:16:21.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}看起来好多了{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}That's looking a lot better.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.77,0:16:23.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}你们是一群分子吗？{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}Do you feel like a bunch of molecules?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.94,0:16:26.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}- 是 - 好的 不错{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}- Yeah! - Okay, okay, this is looking good.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.65,0:16:28.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}队伍两端各有一面大鼓{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}We have a bass drum at each end of the line.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.02,0:16:30.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}你等着瞧{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}You'll see why in a minute.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.16,0:16:32.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}我们要用鼓来表演{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}We'll get things going with this drummer over here.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.28,0:16:35.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}在击鼓之后 请注意发生的事{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}He's gonna hit the drum, and watch what happens.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.74,0:16:40.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}在这个例子中 压力很好地传递着{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}In this case, the pressure is a good healthy shove,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.62,0:16:42.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}从一个学生到另一个学生{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}and it moves from student to student{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.37,0:16:43.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}传遍了整个队伍{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}all the way down the line.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.91,0:16:46.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}最后 末端的学生通过击鼓{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}At the end, the last student applies his pressure{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.90,0:16:48.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}把压力传到了第二面鼓{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}to the second drum by banging on it.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.41,0:16:53.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}第二面鼓就象是我们的耳膜{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}This second drum is like our eardrum.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.99,0:16:57.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}当空气里声波的压力冲击我们的耳膜{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}When pressure from a sound wave in the air hits our eardrums,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.19,0:16:58.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}我们就能听到声音{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}we hear the sound.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.67,0:17:01.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}正如学生的彼此推动{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}This is just how sound travels through the air,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.24,0:17:03.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}空气分子通过彼此推动{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}except instead of having students shoving each other,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.99,0:17:06.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}让声音得以穿过空气{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}there are air molecules shoving each other.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.06,0:17:09.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}声音需要分子来传送{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}A sound needs a medium to travel through.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.55,0:17:12.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}它不能穿越真空{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}It can't travel through a vacuum.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.63,0:17:15.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}所以在实际当中 要从A点去到B点{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}So, in fact, to get from point A to point B,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.17,0:17:17.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}就需要空气分子彼此碰撞{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}you need air molecules hitting each other.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.62,0:17:19.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}这就是它的运作原理{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}That's how it works.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.62,0:17:25.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}那么 第九位的"英仙座沉音"{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}So how do those pressure waves{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.41,0:17:27.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}它的压力波{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}from number nine's "Deep Tones of Perseus"{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.06,0:17:32.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}是如何穿越星系之间的真空地带呢？{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}travel through what's essentially the vacuum of intergalactic space?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.34,0:17:37.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}俄亥俄大学的天体物理学家理查德.波格{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}Astrophysicist Richard Pogge of Ohio State University{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.84,0:17:40.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}让我们在他学校的足球场上{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}gives us a sense of the emptiness in deep space{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.62,0:17:42.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}体验太空深处的虚空{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}at his school's football stadium.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.31,0:17:48.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}虽然声音真的不能穿越宇宙真空{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}While it's true that sound waves can't travel through the vacuum of space,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.06,0:17:49.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}但太空不是完全真空的{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}space is not a complete vacuum.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.67,0:17:51.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}这里是俄亥俄体育馆 七叶树队的主场{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}I'm here at Ohio Stadium, home of the Buckeyes.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.99,0:17:54.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}今天很空旷 我是唯一的人{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}It's very empty today. I'm the only one here.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.14,0:17:57.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}这个场馆能很形象地说明宇宙的真空{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}And I can't think of a better place to illustrate the vacuum of space.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.27,0:18:00.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}空空如也的体育馆可以视为{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}The empty stadium can be a stand-in{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.49,0:18:02.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}宇宙真空的替代物{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}for the vacuum of space{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.19,0:18:05.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}如果与比赛日的盛况相比较的话{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}if we compare it with what it looks like on game day.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.82,0:18:13.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}在超过102 000名观众的情况下{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}With more than 102,000 people in its seats,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.62,0:18:16.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}俄亥俄体育馆如同地球的大气层{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}Ohio Stadium would be like the atmosphere on Earth{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.06,0:18:19.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}空气分子摩肩接踵{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}jam-packed with air molecules.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.62,0:18:23.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}要让体育场怎样空荡荡{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}So how much do we have to clear out this stadium{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.46,0:18:25.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}才相当于宇宙真空呢？{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}to equal the vacuum of space?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.38,0:18:27.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}信不信由你 你要赶走每一个人{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}Believe it or not, you have to clear out everybody,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.19,0:18:29.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}包括我也不例外{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}including me, and then even I'm too much.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.44,0:18:33.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}只有在波格身上的一个细胞也不会留下时{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}No more than a single cell from Pogge's body{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.02,0:18:34.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}才能让俄亥俄体育馆{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}could remain in Ohio Stadium{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.73,0:18:37.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}近似于太空深处的真空{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}to come close to the vacuum of deep space.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.49,0:18:42.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}在英仙座星系团星系之间{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}With what seems like almost nothing in the expanse{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.28,0:18:44.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}看似是空无一物{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}between galaxies of the Perseus cluster,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.57,0:18:49.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}这让声波的存在更显得不可思议{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}the existence of sound waves seems all the more incredible.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.70,0:18:53.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}怎样传送声波 让它穿越极度空洞的太空？{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}How do you propagate a sound wave through empty space when it's mostly empty?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.41,0:18:56.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}就以奔跑在赛场上的我作例子吧{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}Let's use the example of me running down the field.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.71,0:18:58.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}在遇见别人之前 我不停地跑{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}I have to run a long ways before I encounter somebody,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.96,0:19:00.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}遇到别人了{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}but I still encounter somebody,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.30,0:19:02.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}我就把能量传递过去{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}and I can pass energy along to them.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.20,0:19:05.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}在星际空间里的原子也是如此{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}The same is true of atoms in interstellar space.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.43,0:19:08.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}它进行漫漫长征 可能长达300光年{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}It has to travel a long ways, maybe 300 light-years,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.20,0:19:09.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}才会遇到另外的微粒{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}before it encounters another particle,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.77,0:19:11.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}当彼此相遇 它传递能量{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}but when it encounters it, it passes the energy,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.56,0:19:13.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}波就扩散出去{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}and the wave moves along.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.73,0:19:18.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}在英仙座星系团里发生碰撞的微粒{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}The colliding particles in the Perseus cluster{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.30,0:19:21.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}会发射出微弱的X射线{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}also emit faint X-rays whose traces,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.74,0:19:24.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}我们利用钱德拉太空望远镜{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}imaged by the Chandra space telescope,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.08,0:19:26.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}就能知道波在那里{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}tell us the waves are there.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.33,0:19:28.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}但这些波非常多{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}But these waves are huge,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.37,0:19:30.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}而且所产生的音调之低{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}and the notes they produce are lower{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.34,0:19:33.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}是人类从未有遇到过的{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}than anything any human has ever experienced.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.85,0:19:40.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}它的音调比我们听到的钢琴中央A音{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}The pitch is about 57 octaves below our hearing,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.17,0:19:42.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}要低57个八度{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}below the middle of a piano range,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.38,0:19:45.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}这足以让它作为人类知道的最低音调{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}and that actually qualifies this for the Guinness Book of Records{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.48,0:19:48.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}入选《吉尼斯世界记录》{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}as the deepest pitch known to man.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.41,0:19:53.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}这个源自英仙座的极端低音{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}The extreme deep note emanating from Perseus{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.20,0:19:55.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}远远低于我们的听力范围{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}is so far below our hearing range{\r}
