Dialogue: 0,0:30:24.58,0:30:26.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}它看起来很象比萨饼{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}It looks a lot like a pizza.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:30:27.22,0:30:30.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}它是整个太阳系里活动最猛烈的卫星{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}This is the most volcanically active moon in the entire solar system,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:30:30.70,0:30:33.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}比地球的活动猛烈10到100倍{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}10 or 100 times more volcanically active than the Earth.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:30:33.43,0:30:36.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}它每秒向太空喷发{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}It literally spews tons of material{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:30:36.09,0:30:37.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}数以吨计的{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}into space every second...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:30:38.12,0:30:39.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}硫磺和氧原子{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}sulfur and oxygen atoms.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:30:39.85,0:30:43.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}这些物质在木星磁场里成为离子{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}These get ionized in Jupiter's magnetic field{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:30:43.36,0:30:45.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}并反过来影响木星{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}and actually connect back to Jupiter,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:30:45.39,0:30:48.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}在其南北极产生环状物{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}to the north and south poles, making a doughnut.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:30:49.95,0:30:52.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}这个环状物被称为木卫一磁流管{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}The doughnut is called the Io flux tube,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:30:52.66,0:30:55.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}带电粒子在木星和活动猛烈的卫星之间{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}and the charged particles carry a monster electric current{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:30:55.89,0:30:58.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}产生巨大的电流{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}between Jupiter and its volcanic moon.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:30:59.94,0:31:01.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}在伽利略号穿越它的时候…{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}As Galileo flew through it...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:31:03.07,0:31:05.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}声音骤然而来 嘎然而止{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}The sound ended as abruptly as it started.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:31:15.54,0:31:18.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}木星和其卫星的演出告一段落{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}With Jupiter and its moons finishing their acts,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:31:19.48,0:31:21.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}我们的倒数对象 这次是土星{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}our countdown swings to Saturn,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:31:21.77,0:31:25.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}它虽比木星小 但也能入围十大金曲榜{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}smaller than Jupiter but right up there in the top ten.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:31:25.69,0:31:29.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}这个带光环的行星名列第四位{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}The ringed planet comes in at number four on the list.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:31:29.84,0:31:33.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}请仔细听"土星的超现实声音"{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}Listen up for the "Surreal Sounds of Saturn."{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:31:35.92,0:31:38.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}它们是卡西尼号航天器传给我们的{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}They come to us from the Cassini spacecraft,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:31:38.81,0:31:41.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}卡西尼号在2004年到达这个行星后{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}which has been delivering mind-blowing pictures and data{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:31:41.97,0:31:45.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}传回了许多令人兴奋的照片和数据{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}since its arrival at the ringed planet in 2004.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:31:47.75,0:31:49.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}就象旅行者号和伽利略号一样{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}As on Voyager and Galileo,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:31:50.19,0:31:53.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}卡西尼号的等离子体波器{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}Cassini's plasma wave instrument is our proxy{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:31:53.14,0:31:55.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}充当了我们人类在太空里的耳朵{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}for human ears in space.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:31:58.07,0:32:00.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}从卡西尼号的无线电和等离子体波器{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}The eerie and bizarre sounds we hear from{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:32:00.69,0:32:03.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}所听到的声音怪诞奇异{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}Cassini's radio and plasma-wave instrument{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:32:03.64,0:32:05.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}让我们犹如置身于万圣节前夕{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}make me think of Halloween.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:32:08.47,0:32:11.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}它们起源于远比地球极光小得多的土星极光{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}They're due to the aurora on Saturn, very similar to Earth's aurora.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:32:14.78,0:32:16.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}你的耳朵永远听不出这些频率{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}Your ears could never pick up these frequencies,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:32:16.95,0:32:19.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}但把它们转换到一定范围后{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}but we move them into a range, and when we do,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:32:19.35,0:32:22.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}我们会吃惊于它们是多么的怪诞和奇异{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}we were surprised to see how eerie and scary they actually were.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:32:29.77,0:32:31.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}"土星的超现实声音"{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}The "Surreal Sounds of Saturn"{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:32:31.46,0:32:34.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}不是这个带光环的行星唯一的上榜金曲{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}isn't the ringed planet's only song on the countdown.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:32:36.52,0:32:39.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}紧接着的金曲榜第三名是{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}Turn it over, and we find number three on the playlist:{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:32:40.41,0:32:42.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}"土星的另一面"{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}"Saturn's Flip Side."{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:32:45.51,0:32:48.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}科学家称这首歌曲为"交叉"{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}Scientists call this hit a crossover.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:32:48.93,0:32:52.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}这首"交叉"与音乐风格毫无关系{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}This crossover has nothing to do with mixing musical styles{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:32:53.52,0:32:55.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}只是对土星南北半球{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}but describes radio waves{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:32:55.07,0:32:57.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}无线电波波型的描述{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}from Saturn's northern and southern hemispheres,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:32:57.64,0:33:01.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}它们在一个时间周期内会发生频率交叉{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}as they actually crisscross in frequency over a period of time.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:33:04.21,0:33:06.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}我们在无线电数据 等离子体波数据中{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}We saw something really strange in our radio data,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:33:06.73,0:33:08.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}发现相互交叉的一对频率{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}in our plasma-wave data...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:33:08.61,0:33:10.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}这非常奇怪{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}a couple of crossing frequencies{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:33:11.22,0:33:13.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}似乎暗示着南北半球{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}that apparently suggested that the northern{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:33:13.35,0:33:16.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}在以不同速率旋转{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}and southern hemispheres were rotating at different rates.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:33:16.43,0:33:18.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}这在我们固体地球上很不寻常{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}That's very unfamiliar to us on a solid Earth,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:33:18.99,0:33:20.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}地球是以一个速率旋转的{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}where the Earth rotates at one rate.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:33:22.09,0:33:23.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}不过 我们不认为{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}It actually turns out we don't think{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:33:23.82,0:33:25.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}土星是以不同的速率在旋转{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}Saturn's rotating at different rates.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:33:25.39,0:33:28.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}我们认为 高空处的西风带蒙骗了我们{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}We think that high-altitude zonal winds are tricking us{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:33:28.97,0:33:31.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}让我们以为南北半球的{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}and making us think that there's different rotation{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:33:31.66,0:33:33.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}旋转速率不同{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}in the northern and southern hemisphere,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:33:33.30,0:33:34.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}但实情并非如此{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}but it's probably not the case.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:33:39.16,0:33:40.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}类似的波{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}Similar waves,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:33:40.23,0:33:42.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}沿着土星磁场路线分布{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}following the lines of Saturn's magnetic field,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:33:42.85,0:33:45.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}揭露了这个带光环行星的一个神奇现象{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}revealed a surprise about the ringed planet.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:33:47.39,0:33:49.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}卡西尼号所发现的最离奇事情之一是{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}One of the most bizarre things that Cassini found{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:33:49.94,0:33:51.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}土星的一天{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}was apparently the Saturn day{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:33:51.21,0:33:54.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}比数十年前旅行者号探测到的{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}was about six minutes longer than it was back in the days of Voyager,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:33:54.74,0:33:56.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}长了6分钟{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}mere decades earlier.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:33:56.17,0:33:58.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}土星一天的时间长度{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}The determination of the length of Saturn's day{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:33:58.61,0:34:02.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}不能通过观察它周围的云层来测量{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}is actually not possible by watching the clouds rotate around the planet.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:34:02.35,0:34:05.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}我们只能使用射电辐射这些太空声音{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}We have to use these radio emissions, the sounds of space,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:34:05.59,0:34:07.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}来观察内部深层的运行情况{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}to see what the deep interior is doing.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:34:07.86,0:34:09.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}去发现其中奥秘{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}And that's where we found this mystery.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:34:13.18,0:34:16.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}让土星这样块头的行星{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}It's virtually impossible to slow down a planet{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:34:16.05,0:34:19.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}停滞哪怕一瞬间 那是不可能的{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}the size of Saturn that much in such a short time.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:34:20.41,0:34:22.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}所以科学家们认识到{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}So scientists now realize{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:34:22.37,0:34:25.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}射电辐射很可能给不出清晰的照片{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}the radio emissions probably don't give an accurate picture.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:34:27.05,0:34:29.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}靠着对土星风图的精确测绘{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}And by sophisticated mapping of Saturn's winds,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:34:30.16,0:34:32.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}他们现在已经知道{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}they now have a better take on Saturn's day,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:34:33.04,0:34:37.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}土星的一天是10小时34分钟13秒{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}which happens to be 10 hours, 34 minutes, and 13 seconds long.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:34:42.03,0:34:44.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}现在 我们正在接近土卫六泰坦{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}Now we're closing in on the surface of Titan,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:34:45.03,0:34:46.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}它是土星最大的卫星{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}Saturn's biggest moon,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:34:46.54,0:34:49.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}也进入了我们的外域声音排行榜{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}as it swings into the Alien Sounds Countdown.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:34:49.80,0:34:53.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}位居第二的是"非常泰坦"{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}Hit number two rings out as "Totally Titan."{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:34:54.36,0:34:56.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}它以超自然的嘶嘶声作为开始{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}And it opens with an otherworldly hiss{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:34:56.79,0:34:59.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}是卡西尼号在远离地球约十亿英里的地方{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}from an actual microphone on the Huygens lander,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:34:59.78,0:35:01.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}所释放的惠更斯号登陆车{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}separated from Cassini{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:35:01.21,0:35:03.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}在挂着降落伞穿过泰坦的甲烷大气层时{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}and parachuting through Titan's methane atmosphere,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:35:04.10,0:35:06.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}车上的麦克风所捕捉到的{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}nearly a billion miles away from Earth.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:35:08.27,0:35:10.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}在跳伞中 你会听到…{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}If you're parachuting, you're going to hear...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:35:11.69,0:35:14.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}这正是我们在惠更斯号上听到的声音{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}That's exactly what we hear in these Huygens sounds.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:35:18.52,0:35:20.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}在2005年 在登陆车冲向泰坦表面的时候{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}The sound was transmitted as the lander headed{\r}
