Dialogue: 0,0:40:45.94,0:40:49.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}它应当象穿透天文物理介质或物体的{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}and that might be examples of plasma waves{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:40:49.32,0:40:52.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}等离子波和压力这些东西{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}and pressure moving through astrophysical media or objects.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:40:53.46,0:40:57.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}但实际上 如果你从远方观察我们的地球{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}But, really, if you think about observing our Earth from afar,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:40:57.79,0:40:59.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}外星人就是我们{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}the aliens are us.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:40:59.39,0:41:00.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}我们的声音独一无二{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}And our sounds are unique,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:41:00.72,0:41:03.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}因为它来自于活着的生物{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}because they come from living organisms,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:41:03.46,0:41:05.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}它是人类的语言…{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}whether it be human language...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:41:07.33,0:41:08.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}或是鸟儿的歌{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}Or bird songs.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:41:13.75,0:41:16.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}外域探测器扫描地球表面时{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}An alien probe exploring Earth space{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:41:16.31,0:41:19.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}肯定会捕获到与木星或土星相类似的{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}would certainly pick up the Jupiter or Saturn-like sounds{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:41:19.14,0:41:22.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}带电粒子因被地球磁场推动而产生的声音{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}of charged particles propelled by Earth's magnetic field.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:41:25.25,0:41:27.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}但我们的行星 与众不同的是{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}But our planet, unlike the others,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:41:27.32,0:41:29.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}还会发出无线电波{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}also emits radio waves,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:41:30.00,0:41:33.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}在宇宙里昭告人类的存在{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}broadcast into the cosmos by human beings.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:41:40.97,0:41:44.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}晚上好 我是雷吉纳德 A. 费森登教授{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}Good evening, this is Professor Reginald A. Fessenden,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:41:44.76,0:41:47.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}在马萨诸塞州的布兰特洛克镇和你说话{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}speaking to you from Brant Rock, Massachusetts.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:41:48.46,0:41:51.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}1906年 在马萨诸塞州的布兰特洛克镇{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}In 1906, at Brant Rock, Massachusetts,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:41:51.99,0:41:54.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}雷吉纳德.费森登首次利用无线电{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}Reginald Fessenden made the first radio broadcast{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:41:54.95,0:41:56.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}广播了声乐节目{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}of speech and music.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:41:57.99,0:42:00.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}费森登是调幅(AM)广播的发明者{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}Fessenden was the inventor of AM radio,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:42:00.65,0:42:03.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}他在圣诞前夕进行了首次信号传送{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}transmitting his first signals on Christmas Eve.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:42:05.85,0:42:09.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}信号被水手们在数百英里外的海洋上捕捉到{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}It was picked up by sailors hundreds of miles out at sea{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:42:10.81,0:42:14.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}并从此贯穿太空{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}and has been traveling through space ever since.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:42:15.05,0:42:16.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}自从有了无线电{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}Ever since the beginning of radio,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:42:16.71,0:42:19.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}我们一直在向太空发出广播{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}we've really been broadcasting out into space.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:42:19.55,0:42:21.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}我们所发送的这些信号{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}And we've been sending out these signals,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:42:21.49,0:42:23.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}希望有某些人会截获到{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}in the hopes that somebody will intercept them.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:42:24.28,0:42:25.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}当然 太空实在太大了{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}Of course, space is a very large place,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:42:25.91,0:42:27.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}所以 难以知道{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}and, therefore, it's hard to know{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:42:27.71,0:42:29.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}谁会在什么时候收到它们{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}who would have gotten them and when,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:42:29.61,0:42:32.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}但他们会在那里 尽管谁也不知道是哪里{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}but there they are on their way out to who knows where.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:42:36.16,0:42:38.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}地球上的小孩在向您打招呼{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}Hello from the children of Planet Earth.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:42:40.77,0:42:43.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}地球上的声音也在太空里传送着{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}Earthly sounds are also traveling through space,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:42:43.29,0:42:47.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}但靠的不是无线电 而是装载在稳步迈向太空深处的…{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}not by radio, but aboard the two Voyager space probes...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:42:47.99,0:42:51.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}两艘旅行者号上的探测仪{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}on a slow but steady course to the stars.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:42:51.79,0:42:53.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}大家早上好{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}Bonjour, tout le monde.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:42:54.36,0:42:57.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}对地球上的我们来说 声音很重要{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}One of the examples of how important sound is{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:42:57.36,0:43:00.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}所以 在发射旅行者号的时候{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}to us here on Earth is that when we launched Voyager,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:43:00.73,0:43:05.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}我们放上了一张录有地球声音的黄金唱片{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}we actually included a golden record of sounds from our Earth.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:43:05.40,0:43:08.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}其中不仅有人类的声音{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}And this was to represent not only human sound{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:43:08.26,0:43:11.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}还有许多同在地球生活的生物的声音{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}but also sounds of the many creatures that live here on Earth with us.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:43:12.30,0:43:15.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}所以 它实际上是地球生命的声学指纹{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}So it's really a sound fingerprint of life on our planet.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:43:21.30,0:43:22.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}我们以自己的方式{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}As we take our own place{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:43:22.80,0:43:25.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}对十大声音进行的探讨{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}among the top ten hits in our playlist,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:43:26.52,0:43:29.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}对响荡在虚空里的太空声音来说{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}we realize they only scratch the surface{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:43:29.27,0:43:32.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}其实很肤浅{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}of the cosmic voices calling out in the void.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:43:33.15,0:43:35.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}从创世至今{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}From creation to the present day,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:43:36.03,0:43:39.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}宇宙产生了数不胜数的声音{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}space has produced a broad catalog of sounds{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:43:39.15,0:43:41.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}为它的壮丽景色伴奏{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}to accompany its brilliant sights.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:43:42.99,0:43:45.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}这些各种各样的声音似乎很怪异{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}As strange as these many sounds seem,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:43:45.89,0:43:48.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}但我们知道 它们携带着重要信息{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}we've learned that they carry important messages,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:43:49.32,0:43:51.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}能帮助我们去解开自然之谜{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}helping to solve mysteries of nature{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:43:52.26,0:43:56.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}让我们最大程度地去了解宇宙{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}and our ultimate understanding of the universe.{\r}
